place.name: TANSOR
place.gazetteerText: TANSOR, a parish in Oundle district, Northampton; on the river Nen and the Northampton and Peterborough railway, 2 miles NNE of Oundle. Post town, Oundle. Acres, 2,050. Real property, £2,457. Pop., 248. Houses, 58. The manor belongs to the Earl of Westmoreland. The living is a rectory in the diocese of Peterborough. Value, £283.* Patrons, the Dean and Chapter of Lincoln. The church is partly Norman, partly early English. Charities, £39. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
